The nuclear explosion at Chernobyl on the 26th April, 1986, was the worst man-made disaster in history. 50 tonnes of radiation were released into the atmosphere. It contaminated millions of acres of forests and farmlands, causing death and destruction.  The disaster provides insights into the devastating effects of sin. It also provides insights into sinâ€™s cure and reminds us that one day soon, God will set things right and create a new paradise home for us.
